main event: A person reported seeing a bright light in the sky that disappeared behind some trees and could not be located again.
interesting points: The light was of unknown origin and was not pulsating or blinking.
The observer estimated the object to have a very high velocity and not of a natural phenomena moving at the speed of a satellite.
The object seemed to fade a little and immediately disappear after about 10 seconds.
Weather conditions were clear with calm winds.
No photographs or other corroborating evidence was available.
sighted object: a bright light in the sky
witnesses: a single observer, a student at the University of Nebraska
